cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it explores the representational statistics of DNN neurons in the field of computer vision. Additionally, the use of ImageNet, a widely used dataset in computer vision, further supports this categorization. 

The paper also involves optimization and prediction, which suggests a possible fit with the neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. 

The exploration of whether DNN neurons possess image object representational statistics similar to monkey IT neurons suggests a possible fit with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of statistical analysis and modeling of neural responses suggests a possible fit with the neural and information processing (cs.NI) sub-category.
